title: The Gripes
description: The kids complain so much they become actual charity cases. Gumball is in such a bad mood that it spreads to Darwin, who joins him in complaining about everything. Their constant moaning grabs the attention of the good people of Elmore. Mistaking Gumball and Darwin for genuine kids in need, they put on a benefit and raise money for them. How do Gumball and Darwin confess there's been a mix-up without inciting a riot?!!

title: The Joy
description: Miss Simian has to save herself from a contagious Joy virus infecting the whole school. After Dad gives Gumball and Darwin a special hug, the kids go to school filled with a virulent form of Joy. Miss Simian quickly identifies the terrible affliction, and soon enough it spreads to the other kids. She has to find a cure before it's too late. Before Ms Simian herself is won over by . . . Joy.

title: Waiting for Gumball: Telly
description: Grady thinks the TV show they are watching is awful and decides to get the gang together to make their own show.

title: The Name
description: When Mom reveals Gumball's real name is Zach, Gumball adopts a cheesy, annoying persona to match the name. His family tries to make him remember the old Gumball as this new Zach persona is progressively taking over Gumball's life and erasing his memories. If they can't reach him in time, the old Gumball will disappear forever and they'll be left with Zach!

title: Gumball: Elmore News 3
description: From a high-speed police chase to the inside scoop on Daisy the Donkey, Channel 6 Elmore News has all the top hard-hitting local stories. Experienced newscaster Kip Schlezinger is the man to bring you the latest news, sports and weather, even when there is absolutely nothing to report.

title: Waiting for Gumball: Weird Food
description: Puppet Gumball imagines some weird food then tries it.

title: The Fan
description: Sarah, the new kid in school, is Gumball and Darwin's number one, slightly obsessive, fan. Sarah is intensely following Gumball and Darwin around trying to win their friendship.  When Gumball tells her that she is acting like a stalker, she embraces it and actually takes it up a notch.  However, when Gumball and Darwin realise that she's behaving this way because she's lonely, they go to surprising lengths to make her feel accepted.

title: Waiting for Gumball: Spoons
description: Frank has taken Grady's beloved house Spoon. Grady is forced into a dance off to win it back.

title: Gumball: Elmore News 4
description: From a high-speed police chase to the inside scoop on Daisy the Donkey, Channel 6 Elmore News has all the top hard-hitting local stories. Experienced newscaster Kip Schlezinger is the man to bring you the latest news, sports and weather, even when there is absolutely nothing to report.

title: Gumball: Elmore News 1
description: From a high-speed police chase to the inside scoop on Daisy the Donkey, Channel 6 Elmore News has all the top hard-hitting local stories. Experienced newscaster Kip Schlezinger is the man to bring you the latest news, sports and weather, even when there is absolutely nothing to report.

title: The Vacation
description: The Wattersons set off on a relaxing vacation and end up running for their lives! The Wattersons are swapping scary stories on a family vacation, when their car breaks down in the middle of the desert. They are left with no alternative but to trust a complete stranger, whose appearance matches the scary guy in Mom's story. When the stranger brings them to a derelict gas station, just as he did in mom's made-up scary story, the Wattersons can no longer pretend the story isn't coming true . . .

title: Waiting for Gumball: Pineapple
description: Gumball briefly loses his puppet mouth to an enthusiastic Pineapple.

title: The Kids
description: Gumball and Darwin's voices may be breaking, but they're showing no signs of growing up. Whilst Gumball and Darwin make fun of Mom and Dad for being old, their voices start to break. They try to ignore it, but everybody they meet reacts to their new and unpredictable voices. Gumball and Darwin finally decide to make the most of their childhood whilst there's still time.

title: Waiting for Gumball: BirdPlaneBird
description: Darwin and BirdPlaneBird try to share a refreshing drink, it turns out to be hard as a puppet.

title: The Coach
description: The new coach at Elmore High stands up to Jamie. The new Coach witnesses Jamie bullying the other kids at lunch and steps in. Jamie is made to apologise, much to the amazement of the other kids. Gumball and Darwin worry about Jamie seeking revenge, especially when they see him sneaking into the back of Coach's car. They use their newly acquired gym skills to save the Coach from being bullied.

title: Gumball: Elmore News 2
description: From a high-speed police chase to the inside scoop on Daisy the Donkey, Channel 6 Elmore News has all the top hard-hitting local stories. Experienced newscaster Kip Schlezinger is the man to bring you the latest news, sports and weather, even when there is absolutely nothing to report.

title: Waiting for Gumball: Insulting Voices
description: Gumball and Darwin play with smaller hand puppets of themselves who mimic their voices very badly.

title: The Puppy
description: The kids finally get the puppy they always wanted, except . . . it's actually a turtle, and it hates them. After begging Dad for a puppy, the kids are taken aback when he comes home with a turtle. Despite the fact that the turtle turns out to be extremely aggressive (especially toward Gumball) they try their best to give it the love it deserves. This achieves nothing. The Evil Turtle escapes and goes on a rampage, and they have to find it before it destroys Elmore.

title: Waiting for Gumball: Infinite Loop
description: Gumball and Darwin discover smaller hand puppet  versions of themselves and get caught in an infinite loop of puppets.

title: The Extras
description: It's quiet a day for Gumball and Darwin and the background characters finally get their chance to shine. Nothing much is happening for Gumball and Darwin and the background characters in Elmore seize their moment. An array of diverse characters you may have noticed lurking in the background of Gumball and Darwin's adventures finally let their voices be heard. A series of sketches include some tennis crowd extras, two pizzas in love and The Bacon Guy.

title: Waiting for Gumball: Clean
description: Grady is determined to tidy up the house and persuades Howdy and Frank to help. While cleaning Frank unexpectedly discovers the love of his life under a bin bag.

title: Waiting for Gumball: Cool to Be Felt
description: Gumball and Darwin realize they are puppets and it's seriously cool.

title: Waiting for Gumball: Bored
description: Frank is bored and pesters the others to entertain him for the afternoon.

title: The Recipe
description: Gumball and Darwin discover the secret behind Anton's immortality. Anton's little toasty body disintegrates during a swim class. When Gumball and Darwin see Anton the next day, as good as new, they set out to discover his secret. It turns out that his parents use a special formula to bake new Antons when necessary. So the kids test it out at home and end up baking a clone army whose leader - Ant-one - wants to destroy Anton and take over the world.

title: Waiting for Gumball: Gnomes
description: Gumball and Darwin realize that anything they imagine will become real in Puppet World, but all they can think of are Garden Gnomes.

title: Waiting for Gumball: Beards
description: Puppet Gumball and Darwin discover they can grow very weird beards.

title: The People's Song Music Video
description: Secondary characters take the lead in this musical number.

title: Waiting for Gumball: Grump
description: Frank is getting grumpy waiting for Gumball and Darwin to return so Grady and Howdy throw a party to cheer him up.
